---
import { href } from "../lib/href";
import facts from "../generated/facts.json";

const REPO = "https://github.com/crypticpy/build-a-claude-harness";
const sha = (facts as { shortSha?: string }).shortSha ?? "";
const settingsUrl = (facts as { provenance?: { settings?: string } }).provenance?.settings ?? REPO;

const outcomes = [
  "Name the six moments in every session where a builder can change what the AI does.",
  "Explain how one small router runs all of them, so adding a behavior never means rewiring.",
  "Show how the AI keeps its memory across hours of work, even after the conversation gets trimmed.",
  "Say why a second model guards the few actions you can't undo, which is what makes an unattended run safe.",
];
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
    <meta
      name="description"
      content="A visual guide to how Claude Code works, and how one real harness extends it. The model writes the code; the harness decides whether it works. No setup, no code to write."
    />
    <link rel="icon" href={href("favicon.svg")} />
    <title>Harness Atlas — the model writes the code, the harness decides whether it works</title>
  </head>
  <body>
    <header class="topbar">
      <span class="topbar-brand">Harness Atlas</span>
      <span class="topbar-tag">A visual guide · built on Claude Code</span>
    </header>

    <main id="main">
      <section class="hero">
        <p class="eyebrow">How Claude Code actually works</p>
        <h1>The model writes the code.<br />The harness decides whether it works.</h1>
        <p class="lede">
          When an AI builds software, the model gets the credit. But the model only produces words.
          Everything that turns those words into working code happens <em>around</em> it: reading your
          project, choosing a tool, running the checks, remembering what it already tried. That
          surrounding machine is the harness. This is a visual tour of one real harness built on Claude
          Code, shown plainly enough that you don't need to write code to follow it.
        </p>
        <p class="thesis">
          An AI coding harness is not the model. It is the operating environment that turns model
          reasoning into reliable software work.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="start" aria-labelledby="start-h">
        <h2 id="start-h">Start with the loop.</h2>
        <p class="start-lede">
          Before any of the machinery makes sense, you need one idea: Claude Code runs in a loop. It
          reads, plans, acts, checks its own work, and goes again. Watch that loop turn one plain
          request into finished code. Then we open the real harness and show every part.
        </p>
        <div class="start-cards">
          <a class="card card--primary" href={href("agent-loop")}>
            <span class="card-tag">Begin here · 2 minutes</span>
            <span class="card-title">Watch the agent loop</span>
            <span class="card-sub">
              One plain request, six steps, a strong harness against a weak one. The whole idea in a
              single scroll.
            </span>
            <span class="card-go">Watch it run →</span>
          </a>
          <a class="card" href={href("how-it-works")}>
            <span class="card-tag">Then · the real machine</span>
            <span class="card-title">Open this harness</span>
            <span class="card-sub">
              The same loop, now wired to a real settings file: six lifecycle moments, one router, and a
              memory that survives between sessions.
            </span>
            <span class="card-go">See how it's wired →</span>
          </a>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="outcomes" aria-labelledby="outcomes-h">
        <h2 id="outcomes-h">By the end, you can</h2>
        <ul class="outcomes-list">
          {
            outcomes.map((o) => (
              <li class="outcome">
                <span class="outcome-mark" aria-hidden="true">→</span>
                <span>{o}</span>
              </li>
            ))
          }
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="phases" aria-labelledby="phases-h">
        <h2 id="phases-h">The full teardown, in two phases</h2>
        <p class="phases-lede">
          Sixteen short modules take the harness apart, one piece at a time. Start the loop above first;
          these go deeper once the shape is familiar.
        </p>
        <nav class="phase-nav" aria-label="Phases">
          <a class="phase-card" href={href("phase-1")}>
            <span class="phase-tag">Phase 1 · 8 modules</span>
            <span class="phase-title">Foundations</span>
            <span class="phase-sub">
              The building blocks: lifecycle moments, the router, fail-safe hooks, the memory stack,
              commands, skills, subagents, and MCP.
            </span>
            <span class="phase-go">Begin Phase 1 →</span>
          </a>
          <a class="phase-card" href={href("phase-2")}>
            <span class="phase-tag">Phase 2 · 8 modules</span>
            <span class="phase-title">The teardown</span>
            <span class="phase-sub">
              A guided teardown of the reference harness, layer by layer, up to the approval gate that
              keeps a long, unattended run safe.
            </span>
            <span class="phase-go">Begin Phase 2 →</span>
          </a>
        </nav>
      </section>

      <section class="closing">
        {
          sha && (
            <p class="prov">
              Every claim links to the exact line of the real harness it came from, pinned to commit{" "}
              <a href={settingsUrl} rel="noopener"><code>{sha}</code></a>. Nothing here is invented for
              the lesson.
            </p>
          )
        }
        <p class="closing-links">
          <a href={href("agent-loop")}>Start with the agent loop →</a>
          <a href={REPO} rel="noopener">Source on GitHub</a>
        </p>
      </section>
    </main>

    <style is:global>
      :root {
        --paper: #fbfaf6;
        --paper-2: #ffffff;
        --ink: #221f1a;
        --ink-soft: #5c554b;
        --ink-faint: #968d7d;
        --hair: #e6e0d4;
        --hair-strong: #d6cdbb;
        --context: #2f6bd8;
        --action: #c9740a;
        --verified: #1f9a63;
        --risk: #d6453f;
        --serif: "Iowan Old Style", "Palatino Linotype", Palatino, "Book Antiqua", Georgia, ui-serif,
          serif;
        --sans: ui-sans-serif, system-ui, -apple-system, "Segoe UI", Roboto, Helvetica, Arial,
          sans-serif;
        --mono: ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, "SF Mono", Menlo, Consolas, monospace;
      }

      * {
        box-sizing: border-box;
      }
      html {
        scroll-behavior: smooth;
      }
      body {
        margin: 0;
        background: var(--paper);
        color: var(--ink);
        font-family: var(--sans);
        -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;
        text-rendering: optimizeLegibility;
      }

      .topbar {
        display: flex;
        align-items: center;
        justify-content: space-between;
        padding: 18px clamp(20px, 5vw, 56px);
        border-bottom: 1px solid var(--hair);
        position: sticky;
        top: 0;
        background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--paper) 92%, transparent);
        z-index: 20;
      }
      .topbar-brand {
        font-family: var(--serif);
        font-weight: 600;
        font-size: 17px;
        color: var(--ink);
      }
      .topbar-tag {
        font-family: var(--mono);
        font-size: 12px;
        letter-spacing: 0.06em;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        color: var(--ink-faint);
      }

      main {
        max-width: 1180px;
        margin: 0 auto;
        padding: 0 clamp(20px, 5vw, 56px);
      }

      .eyebrow {
        font-family: var(--mono);
        font-size: 12.5px;
        letter-spacing: 0.13em;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        color: var(--action);
        margin: 0 0 14px;
      }

      /* ---- hero / cold open ---- */
      .hero {
        padding: clamp(56px, 11vh, 128px) 0 clamp(32px, 6vh, 64px);
        max-width: min(74ch, 100%);
      }
      .hero h1 {
        font-family: var(--serif);
        font-weight: 600;
        font-size: clamp(34px, 6vw, 64px);
        line-height: 1.05;
        letter-spacing: -0.015em;
        margin: 0 0 28px;
      }
      .lede {
        font-size: clamp(18px, 2.2vw, 22px);
        line-height: 1.55;
        color: var(--ink-soft);
        max-width: 60ch;
        margin: 0 0 32px;
      }
      .lede em {
        font-style: normal;
        color: var(--ink);
        border-bottom: 2px solid color-mix(in srgb, var(--action) 55%, transparent);
        padding-bottom: 1px;
      }
      .thesis {
        font-family: var(--serif);
        font-size: clamp(19px, 2.4vw, 25px);
        line-height: 1.4;
        color: var(--ink);
        max-width: 52ch;
        margin: 0;
        padding-left: 20px;
        border-left: 3px solid var(--action);
      }

      /* ---- section heads ---- */
      .start,
      .outcomes,
      .phases {
        padding-block: clamp(40px, 8vh, 88px) 0;
      }
      .start h2,
      .outcomes h2,
      .phases h2 {
        font-family: var(--serif);
        font-weight: 600;
        font-size: clamp(26px, 3.6vw, 40px);
        line-height: 1.1;
        letter-spacing: -0.012em;
        margin: 0 0 16px;
      }
      .start-lede,
      .phases-lede {
        font-size: clamp(17px, 2vw, 20px);
        line-height: 1.6;
        color: var(--ink-soft);
        max-width: 58ch;
        margin: 0 0 32px;
      }

      /* ---- start cards ---- */
      .start-cards {
        display: grid;
        gap: clamp(16px, 2.5vw, 24px);
        grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
      }
      .card {
        display: flex;
        flex-direction: column;
        gap: 8px;
        padding: clamp(22px, 3vw, 32px);
        background: var(--paper-2);
        border: 1px solid var(--hair);
        border-radius: 16px;
        text-decoration: none;
        color: var(--ink);
        box-shadow:
          0 1px 2px rgba(40, 38, 32, 0.04),
          0 16px 36px -28px rgba(40, 38, 32, 0.22);
        transition:
          border-color 0.16s ease,
          transform 0.12s ease,
          box-shadow 0.16s ease;
      }
      .card:hover {
        transform: translateY(-2px);
        border-color: var(--hair-strong);
        box-shadow:
          0 1px 2px rgba(40, 38, 32, 0.05),
          0 24px 48px -28px rgba(40, 38, 32, 0.28);
      }
      .card--primary {
        border-color: color-mix(in srgb, var(--action) 45%, var(--hair));
        background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--action) 5%, var(--paper-2));
      }
      .card--primary:hover {
        border-color: var(--action);
      }
      .card-tag {
        font-family: var(--mono);
        font-size: 12px;
        letter-spacing: 0.08em;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        color: var(--action);
      }
      .card-title {
        font-family: var(--serif);
        font-size: clamp(21px, 2.6vw, 27px);
        font-weight: 600;
        line-height: 1.15;
      }
      .card-sub {
        font-size: 16px;
        line-height: 1.55;
        color: var(--ink-soft);
        margin-top: 2px;
      }
      .card-go {
        margin-top: auto;
        padding-top: 14px;
        font-weight: 600;
        font-size: 15px;
        color: var(--context);
      }

      /* ---- outcomes ---- */
      .outcomes-list {
        list-style: none;
        margin: 0;
        padding: 0;
        display: grid;
        gap: 16px 40px;
        grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
        max-width: 90ch;
      }
      .outcome {
        display: flex;
        gap: 14px;
        align-items: baseline;
        font-size: clamp(16px, 1.8vw, 18px);
        line-height: 1.5;
        color: var(--ink-soft);
      }
      .outcome-mark {
        color: var(--action);
        font-weight: 700;
        flex: none;
      }

      /* ---- phases ---- */
      .phase-nav {
        display: grid;
        gap: clamp(16px, 2.5vw, 24px);
        grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
      }
      .phase-card {
        display: flex;
        flex-direction: column;
        gap: 6px;
        padding: clamp(22px, 3vw, 30px);
        background: var(--paper-2);
        border: 1px solid var(--hair);
        border-radius: 16px;
        text-decoration: none;
        color: var(--ink);
        transition:
          border-color 0.16s ease,
          transform 0.12s ease;
      }
      .phase-card:hover {
        transform: translateY(-2px);
        border-color: var(--hair-strong);
      }
      .phase-tag {
        font-family: var(--mono);
        font-size: 12px;
        letter-spacing: 0.08em;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        color: var(--ink-faint);
      }
      .phase-title {
        font-family: var(--serif);
        font-size: clamp(20px, 2.4vw, 26px);
        font-weight: 600;
      }
      .phase-sub {
        font-size: 16px;
        line-height: 1.55;
        color: var(--ink-soft);
        margin-top: 2px;
      }
      .phase-go {
        margin-top: 10px;
        font-weight: 600;
        font-size: 15px;
        color: var(--context);
      }

      /* ---- closing ---- */
      .closing {
        padding: clamp(48px, 9vh, 104px) 0 clamp(72px, 14vh, 140px);
        max-width: 72ch;
      }
      .prov {
        font-size: 15px;
        line-height: 1.6;
        color: var(--ink-faint);
        border-top: 1px solid var(--hair);
        padding-top: 22px;
        margin: 0 0 24px;
      }
      .prov code {
        font-family: var(--mono);
        background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--action) 9%, var(--paper-2));
        padding: 1px 7px;
        border-radius: 6px;
        color: var(--action);
      }
      .prov a {
        text-decoration: none;
      }
      .closing-links {
        display: flex;
        flex-wrap: wrap;
        gap: 14px 28px;
        margin: 0;
      }
      .closing-links a {
        color: var(--context);
        text-decoration: none;
        font-weight: 600;
        font-size: 16px;
      }
      .closing-links a:hover {
        text-decoration: underline;
      }

      @media (max-width: 760px) {
        .start-cards,
        .phase-nav,
        .outcomes-list {
          grid-template-columns: 1fr;
        }
      }

      @media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
        html {
          scroll-behavior: auto;
        }
        .card,
        .phase-card {
          transition: none;
        }
      }
    </style>
  </body>
</html>
